                <expan><abbr><supplied reason="lost">I</supplied>mp</abbr><ex>erator</ex></expan> Caesar <lb n="2"/>Vespasianus <lb n="3"/>Augustus <expan><abbr>trib</abbr><ex>unicia</ex></expan> <expan><abbr>pot</abbr><ex>estate</ex></expan> X <lb n="4"/><supplied reason="lost"><expan><abbr>Imp</abbr><ex>erator</ex></expan></supplied> Titus Caesar <lb n="5"/>Augusti <expan><abbr>f</abbr><ex>ilius</ex></expan> <expan><abbr>trib</abbr><ex>unicia</ex></expan> <expan><abbr>pot</abbr><ex>estate</ex></expan> VIII <lb n="6"/><expan><abbr>pub</abbr><ex>lice</ex></expan> <expan><abbr>d</abbr><ex>ecreto</ex></expan> <expan><abbr>d</abbr><ex>ecurionum</ex></expan> </ab></div><div n="2" type="textpart"><ab><lb n="1"/> A<gap reason="lost" extent="unknown" unit="character"/> <lb n="2"/><expan><abbr>Ti</abbr><ex>berius</ex></expan> C<supplied reason="lost">aesa</supplied>r divi Augusti <expan><abbr>f</abbr><ex>ilius</ex></expan> <lb n="3"/>Divi <expan><abbr><supplied reason="lost">Iuli</supplied>n</abbr><ex>epos</ex></expan> <expan><abbr>trib</abbr><ex>unicia</ex></expan> potes<supplied reason="lost"><expan><abbr>t</abbr><ex>ate</ex></expan></supplied> XXXIIX <lb n="4"/>Dru<supplied reason="lost">sus</supplied> Caesar <expan><abbr>Ti</abbr><ex>beri</ex></expan> <expan><abbr>Aug</abbr><ex>usti</ex></expan> <expan><abbr>f</abbr><ex>ilius</ex></expan> <lb n="5"/>divi <supplied reason="lost"><expan><abbr>Aug</abbr><ex>usti</ex></expan> <expan><abbr>n</abbr><ex>epos</ex></expan></supplied> Divi Iuli pro<supplied reason="lost"><expan><abbr>n</abbr><ex>epos</ex></expan></supplied> <expan><abbr>tr</abbr><ex>ibunicia</ex></expan> <expan><abbr>pot</abbr><ex>estate</ex></expan> II </ab></div><div n="3" type="textpart"><ab><lb n="1"/> Cad<supplied reason="lost">m</supplied>us Atimetus Marti<supplied reason="lost" cert="low">alis</supplied> <lb n="2"/><expan><abbr>C</abbr><ex>ai</ex></expan> Iuli <supplied reason="lost">A</supplied>ugusti liberti <expan><abbr>mo</abbr><ex>numentum</ex></expan> <expan><abbr>d</abbr><ex>e</ex></expan> <supplied reason="lost"><expan><abbr>s</abbr><ex>uo</ex></expan> <expan><abbr>f</abbr><ex>aciendum</ex></expan> <expan><abbr>c</abbr><ex>uravit</ex></expan></supplied>
            </ab></div></div>
            <div type="commentary">
                <p>Von der ursprünglichen Platte sind nur noch zwei große Teile vorhanden. Der linke Teil, der die Ehreninschrift für Vespasianus trägt, besteht aus vier zusammengehörenden Fragmente, die die Maße: Höhe 90; Breite 94 cm aufweisen. Die Maße des rechten aus funf Fragmenten bestehenden Teils sind: Höhe 76; Breite 92 cm.</p>
